ies]]\n|Felicity Huffman, Timothy Hutton, W. Earl Brown, Regina King, Richard Cabral, Caitlin Gerard, Benito Martinez, Penelope Ann Miller, Elvis Nolasco, and Johnny Ortiz\n|{{won}}\n|-\n|rowspan=5|[[NAACP Image Award|47th NAACP Image Awards]]<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/naacp-image-award-nominees-full-846814 |title='Creed,' 'Empire' Top NAACP Image Award Nominations; Full List |work=The Hollywood Reporter |date=December 8, 2015 |accessdate=December 12, 2015}}</ref>\n|[[NAACP Image Award for Outstanding Television Movie, Mini-Series or Dramatic Special|Outstanding Television Movie, Mini-Series or Dramatic Special]]\n|''American Crime''\n|{{nom}}\n|-\n|[[NAACP Image Award for Outstanding Supporting Actress in a Drama Series|Outstanding Supporting Actress in a Drama Series]]\n|Regina King\n|{{won}}\n|-\n|rowspan=2|Outstanding Director in a Drama Series\n|John Ridley <br> (Episode: \"Episode One\")\n|{{won}}\n|-\n|[[Millicent Shelton]] <br> (Episode: \"Episode Ten\")\n|{{nom}}\n|-\n|Outstanding Writer in a Drama Series\n|John Ridley <br> (Episode: \"Episode One\")\n|{{nom}}\n|-\n|rowspan=4|[[73rd Golden Globe Awards]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tvline.com/2016/01/10/golden-globe-award-winners-2016-full-list/|title=Golden Globes: ''Mr. Robot'' and ''Mozart'' Win Big; Taraji P. Henson, Lady Gaga, Jon Hamm, Rachel Bloom Grab Gold|website=TVLine|first=Matt Webb|last=Mitovich|date=January 10, 2016|accessdate=January 11, 2016}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Golden Globe Award for Best Miniseries or Television Film|Best Miniseries or Television Film]]\n| ''American Crime''\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[Golden Globe Award for Best Actress \u2013 Miniseries or Television Film|Best Actress \u2013 Miniseries or Television Film]]\n| Felicity Huffman\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[Golden Globe Award for Best Supporting Actress \u2013 Series, Miniseries or Television Film|Best Supporting Actress \u2013 Series, Miniseries or Television Film]]\n| Regina King\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n|colspan=5|<center>'''Season 2'''</center>\n|-\n|rowspan=4|[[68th Primetime Emmy Awards]]<ref>{{cite news|url=https://variety.com/2016/tv/awards/2016-emmys-nominees-list-drama-comedy-acting-nomination-1201814021/|title=Emmy Nominations 2016: Full List of Nominees|work=Variety|first=Laura|last=Prudom|date=July 14, 2016|accessdate=July 14, 2016}}</ref>\n| Outstanding Limited Series\n| ''American Crime''\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |Outstanding Lead Actress in a Limited Series or Movie\n| Felicity Huffman\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[Lili Taylor]]\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Outstanding Supporting Actress in a Limited Series or Movie\n| Regina King <br> (Episode: \"Season Two: Episode Eight\")\n| {{won}}\n|-\n|rowspan=3|[[7th Critics' Choice Television Awards]]<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.ew.com/article/2016/12/11/critics-choice-awards-2016-winners|title=Critics' Choice Awards 2016 winners list: La La Land, People v. O.J dominate|work=Entertainment Weekly|date=December 11, 2016|accessdate=December 12, 2016}}</ref>\n| rowspan=\"2\" |Best Actress in a Movie or Limited Series\n| Felicity Huffman\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Lili Taylor\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Best Supporting Actress in a Movie or Limited Series\n| Regina King\n| {{won}}\n|-\n|rowspan=2|[[74th Golden Globe Awards]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tvline.com/2016/12/12/golden-globe-nominations-2017-globes-awards-nominees/|title=Golden Globes: People v. O.J. Simpson, Night Manager, This Is Us, Westworld, The Crown, black-ish Lead TV Nominees|website=TVLine|first=Matt Webb|last=Mitovich|date=December 12, 2016|accessdate=December 12, 2016}}</ref>\n| Best Miniseries or Television Film\n| ''American Crime''\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Best Actress \u2013 Miniseries or Television Film\n| Felicity Huffman\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n|[[23rd Screen Actors Guild Awards]]<ref>{{cite news| url= http://www.ew.com/article/2016/12/14/2017-sag-awards-nominations | title= SAG Awards nominations 2017: See the full list| first= Joey |last= Nolfi |work= Entertainment Weekly|date= December 14, 2016 